- class that is declared inside class

Advantage :
1. make our code clean & readable
2. optimizing the code module
3. private methods of outer class can be accessed

Types of Inner class:
1. Nested Inner class
2. Method Local Inner class
3. Static Nested class
4. Anonymous Inner class
	- declared without name

Homework:

class outer{
	void outerMethod(){
	int n = 75;//local non-final variable
		class Inner{
			innerMethod(){
				print n
			}
		}
	}
}

2. private,protected,abstract,final

Notes:
1. local inner class cannot access non-final local variable till JDK 1.7.
	since JDK 1.8, it is possible to access non-final local variable